  "persona": "neutral",
  "description": "Generic English longform profile and the default for `tacheles check`. Full anti-AI-slop linter for essays/blog posts/articles: all surface tells, the 7 rhythm tells, and King concision are on, mirroring the strict longform register. Carries NO per-author calibration: em-dash density, sentence/paragraph burstiness (r-uniform-polish), and k-passive use the registry's generic defaults rather than any individual writer's fingerprint, so it works out-of-box on any author's prose. Clone this and tune params/exclude-lists to calibrate to a specific voice. Only k-length-cut (a two-draft delta metric) is off in the linter.",
